TY  - JOUR
AU  - Merlob, Brian
AU  - Plott, Charles R.
AU  - Zhang, Yuanjun
T1  - The CMS Auction: Experimental Studies of a Median-Bid Procurement Auction with Nonbinding Bids*
PY  - 2012
Y1  - 2012/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/qje/qjs013
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 127
IS  - 2
SP  - 793
EP  - 827
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We report on the experimental results of simple auctions with (i) a median-bid pricing rule and (ii) nonbinding bids (winning bids can be withdrawn)—the two central pillars of the competitive bidding program designed by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS). Comparisons between the performance of the CMS auction and the performance of the excluded-bid auction reveal the problematic nature of the CMS auction. The CMS auction fails to generate competitive prices of goods and fails to satisfy demand. In all proposed efficiency measures, we find the excluded-bid auction significantly outperforms the CMS auction.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/qje/qjs013
ER  - 



