AU  - Michaels, Guy
AU  - Rauch, Ferdinand
AU  - Redding, Stephen J.
T1  -  Urbanization and Structural Transformation *
PY  - 2012
Y1  - 2012/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/qje/qjs003
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 127
IS  - 2
SP  - 535
EP  - 586
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We examine urbanization using new data that allow us to track the evolution of population in rural and urban areas in the United States from 1880 to 2000. We find a positive correlation between initial population density and subsequent population growth for intermediate densities, which increases the dispersion of the population density distribution over time. We use theory and empirical evidence to show this pattern of population growth is the result of differences in agriculture's initial share of employment across population densities, combined with structural transformation that shifts employment away from agriculture.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/qje/qjs003
ER  - 



